nd Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Hulton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Lancashire): habitational name from Hulton (Lancashire) or Hulton (Staffordshire), both from Old English <i>hyll</i> ‘hill’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’. Compare   Hilton  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Hilton","meanings":["English (Lancashire):","habitational name from any of various places called Hilton (e.g. in Cambridgeshire, Derbyshire, Staffordshire, North Yorkshire, and Westmorland), most of which derive from Old English <i>hyll</i> ‘hill’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’, though some come from Old English <i>helde</i> ‘slope’ + <i>tūn</i>.","occasionally, as in the case of Ralph <i>filius Hilton</i> (Yorkshire 1219), perhaps from the personal name <i>Hilton</i>, itself a possible form of Norman <i>Hildun</i>, composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>hild</i> ‘strife, battle’ + <i>hūn</i> ‘bear cub’. Compare   Hilt  . This English surname is present in Ireland (mainly taken to Ulster in the early 17th century, though recorded earlier in Dublin)."]}]},{"name":"Bleythin","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["Welsh:  see  Blethyn  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Blything","meanings":["English: variant of   Blythin  ."]},{"name":"Blethyn","meanings":["Welsh: relationship name from the Middle Welsh personal name  <i>Blethyn</i> (Old Welsh  <i>Bledgint</i>, from  <i>bleid</i> ‘wolf’ + apparently the mutated form of  <i>cint</i> ‘first’). The variants in  <i>P-</i> are from  <i>ap Blethyn</i> in which /bp/ was assimilated to /p/."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Bleythin de Hulton was born about 1120, in Prestatyn, Flintshire, Wales, United Kingdom, his father, Bleythin ap Madog, was 26 and his mother, Nigel de Néville, was 38. He had at least 2 sons. He died in 1162, in Over Hulton, Lancashire, England, at the age of 43."},"et":{"about 1120–1162":"umbes 1120–1162","1120–1162":"1120–1162","1145–1215":"1145–1215","1145–Male":"1145–Surnud","1095–1162":"1095–1162","1083–Female":"1083–Surnud","1215":"1215","1145":"1145","1120":"1120","1162":"1162","1095":"1095","1083":"1083","about 1120":"umbes 1120","Wales":"Wales","Prestatyn, Flintshire, Wales":"Prestatyn, Flintshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Over Hulton, Lancashire, England":"Over Hulton, Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"about 1120–1162":"noin 1120–1162","1120–1162":"1120–1162","1145–1215":"1145–1215","1145–Male":"1145–Kuollut","1095–1162":"1095–1162","1083–Female":"1083–Kuollut","1215":"1215","1145":"1145","1120":"1120","1162":"1162","1095":"1095","1083":"1083","about 1120":"noin 1120","Wales":"Wales","Prestatyn, Flintshire, Wales":"Prestatyn, Flintshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Over Hulton, Lancashire, England":"Over Hulton, Lancashire, England"},"fr":{"about 1120–1162":"environ 1120–1162","1120–1162":"1120–1162","1145–1215":"1145–1215","1145–Male":"1145–Décédé","1095–1162":"1095–1162","1083–Female":"1083–Décédée","1215":"1215","1145":"1145","1120":"1120","1162":"1162","1095":"1095","1083":"1083","about 1120":"environ 1120","Wales":"Galles","Prestatyn, Flintshire, Wales":"Prestatyn, Flintshire, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","Over Hulton, Lancashire, England":"Over Hulton, Lancashire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Bleythin de Hulton est né environ 1120, à Prestatyn, Flintshire, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni, son père, Bleythin ap Madog, avait 26 ans et sa mère, Nigel de Néville, avait 38 ans. Il a eu au moins 2 fils. Il est décédé en 1162, à Over Hulton, Lancashire, Angleterre, à l’âge de 43 ans."},"de":{"about 1120–1162":"um 1120–1162","1120–1162":"1120–1162","1145–1215":"1145–1215","1145–Male":"1145–Verstorben","1095–1162":"1095–1162"